#X text 16 482 Tape machines and record players can record and reproduce
sounds in their original form - as continuous signals. Because of the
way computers and other devices such as CD players deal with information
- they just store and recall numbers - the best we can do is approximate
the shape of a sound. Essentially \, the computer takes thousands of
snapshots per second \, storing this information.;
#X text 12 45 Sound is our interpretation of vibrations caused by rapid
changes in air pressure. Sound is usually represented visually on a
graph \, with x representing time and y representing pressure.;
